# Frontend Coding Standards

## Naming Conventions
| Element | Convention | Example |
|:--------|:-----------|:--------|
| Component files | `kebab-case.tsx` | `employee-list.tsx` |
| Utility files | `kebab-case.ts` | `format-date.ts` |
| Components | `PascalCase` | `EmployeeList` |
| Hooks | `useCamelCase` | `useEmployees` |
| Zustand stores | `useCamelCaseStore` | `useSidebarStore` |
| Types | `PascalCase` | `Employee`, `ActivitySnapshot` |
| Route segments | `kebab-case` | `/workforce/live` |

## Component Rules
- Default to **Client Components** (most pages are interactive dashboards)
- Use Server Components only for: static pages, initial data fetch, layout wrappers
- One component per file (except small private helpers used only in that file)
- Export component as named export, not default
- Props interface named `{Component}Props`

## Data Fetching
- **ALWAYS** use TanStack Query hooks — never `useEffect` + `useState`
- Custom hooks per resource: `useEmployees()`, `useExceptionAlerts()`
- Query key convention: `['resource', { ...params }]`
- Mutations invalidate related query keys on success

## Forms
- Zod schema defined ABOVE the component
- `useForm` with `zodResolver`
- Submit via TanStack Query mutation

## Styling
- Tailwind utilities only — no custom CSS unless unavoidable
- shadcn/ui for all base components
- Never use inline `style={}` attributes
- Responsive: desktop-first, must work on tablet (>=768px)

## Error Handling
- API errors: show toast via global error handler (RFC 7807 Problem Details)
- Permission denied: redirect to 403 page
- Network failure: show retry button

## Testing
- Vitest for hooks and utilities (pure logic)
- React Testing Library for components (test behavior, not implementation)
- MSW for API mocking
- No snapshot tests
